RSA CTF Notes 

It contains 3 parts
part1: Key Generation

Select  p,q             p and q are prime numbers; p!=q
Calculate n             n = p * q
Calculate phi(ϕ)        ϕ = ( p - 1 ) * ( q - 1 )
Select integer e        GCD ( ϕ(n) , e ) = 1; 1 < e < ϕ(n)
Calculate d             d = inverse(e) % ϕ(n)
Public Key (Pk)         {e,n}
Private Key (Pr)        {d,n}

Part2: Encryption       

Plain Text (M)          M < n
Cipher Text (C)         C = pow( M , e) % n

Part3: Decryption

Cipher Text (C)         C
Plain Text (M)          M = pow(C , d) % n
